OL,7,FInflation rates have slowed to 6.8%
OL,8,Fin July, down from 7.9% in June, that
OL,9,Fmeans prices are still going up, but
OL,10,Fjust not as much as they were
OL,12,FInflation slowed to its lowest for 17
OL,13,Fmonths in July due to a fall in
OL,14,Fenergy prices and a slowdown in food
OL,15,Fprice increases, according to
OL,16,Fofficial figures.
OL,18,FThe Office for National Statistics
OL,19,F(ONS) said Consumer Prices Index
OL,20,Finflation was 6.8% in July, down from
OL,21,F7.9% in June.
OL,3,CUK inflation falls sharply for second
OL,4,Cmonth to 6.8% as cost of living
OL,5,Cpressures ease
